Prosecuting attorney Jill L. Vendetti in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Diana Marie Brown in court.  Attorney Eric Paul Pitsch in court for Diana Marie Brown. 
State moves to delete the alcohol fine enhancer.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST to the charge in count 1, OWI (3rd) with passenger <16 yrs old.  Convicted. 
State moves to dismiss count 2.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld and defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation: 
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Pay $2,400 fine plus costs, total $4,121.00
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) Provide DNA sample
8) Spend seven (7) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, to commence immediately.
Defendant has 6 days credit if revoked.
 Four (4) year license revocation and three (3) year ignition interlock device requirement are also ordered.
